<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10388> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10231> ;
    skos:definition "Define Technology Migration Risks- As part of the implementation of Migration Assurance Processes a set of KPIs are defined based on potential risks associated with the revenue leakage and customer experience of provisioning and billing errors before, during the testing and after the technology migration.<br/>The revenue assurance tool should be able to use automated control-monitoring mechanisms to ensure that the KPIs meet the defined objectives as well as whenever deviations are detected; the cases are escalated for an immediate resolution to achieve operational control objectives.<br/><br/>The responsibilities of the processes include, but are not limited to:<br/>• Definition of the key risks associated with technology migration form the revenue and customer experience perspective<br/>• Definition of the Business Assurance automated auditing indicators by defining KPIs, controls, and metrics to feed into the Business Assurance tools<br/>• Define the data sources and the data integration procedures in the business assurance tool to monitor risks, if possible in real-time, to feed business assurance KPIs<br/>• Definition of segregation of duties and responsibilities for case escalation and resolution<br/>• Allow the ad hoc analysis of low-level investigations driven by request of stakeholders based on triggered alarms and developed by expert judgment outside of the designed KPIs<br/>• Testing and fine-tuning of the controls in place<br/>• Measure and quantify the impacts of the controls in place during the detection, prevention, and recovery for business <br/>• Implement automatic reporting capabilities for business and operational items previously mentioned<br/>• Documentation (control / metric attributes, dataflow)<br/>• Updated repositories<br/>This process was renamed in 24.0 Old process name Manage Migration Assurance Framework<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10388" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Technology Migration Risks"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10389> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10231> ;
    skos:definition "The Define Migration Assurance Controls and Metrics establishes principles that guide the migration process and sets out controls and metrics recommendations for Communication Service Providers (CSPs) that look for a seamless transition for the technology that supports the services provided to consumers and businesses.<br/>The primary goal the migration assurance framework is to guarantee an accurate, timely and consistent information between the legacy and the new system in place, in order to avoid revenue assurance or customer experience issues.<br/><br/>The responsibilities of the processes include, but are not limited to:<br/>• Definition of the Business Assurance automated auditing indicators by defining KPIs, controls, and metrics to feed into the Business Assurance tools<br/>• Testing and fine-tuning of the controls in place<br/>• Measure and quantify the impacts of the controls in place during the detection, prevention, and recovery for business <br/>• Documentation (control / metric attributes, dataflow)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10389" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Migration Assurance Controls and Metrics"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10390> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10509> ;
    skos:definition "Plan Logistics activity handles the transportation plan, storage plan to support the core (product, service, resource) processes according to the Supply Chain Strategic Management plan.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10390" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Plan Logistics"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10391> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10509> ;
    skos:definition "Plan Sourcing business activity support procurement business activities by providing the blueprint to assess and manage changes so that the benefits of procurement strategies are realized.<br/>Sourcing plan must be created in a way that ensures the benefits identified in the strategy are delivered in full and on time.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10391" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Plan Sourcing Execution"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10392> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10509> ;
    skos:definition "Handle Demand Planning business activity is in charge of forecasting, or predicting, the demand for \"products\" to ensure the enterprise they can be delivered, and that they satisfy customers.<br/>This business activity has a goal of attaining a balance between having sufficient inventory levels to meet customer needs without having a surplus.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10392" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Handle Demand Planning"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10393> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10509> ;
    skos:definition "Plan Supply Network business activity is in charge of integrating purchasing, production, distribution, and transportation so that comprehensive tactical planning and sourcing decisions can be simulated and implemented on the basis of a single, global consistent model.<br/>Plan Supply Network business activity uses advanced optimization activities, based on constraints and penalties, to plan product flow along the supply chain in order to facilitate optimal purchasing, production, and distribution decisions; reduced order fulfillment times and inventory levels; and improved customer service.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10393" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Plan Supply Network"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10394> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10509> ;
    skos:definition "Pan Distribution business activity is in charge of determining the right quality of products to be availed to the enterprises' distribution network in order to meet customer demand.<br/>Plan Distribution ensures that customer and forecasted demand are translated into purchase orders. This process depends on actual demand signals such as customer orders, as those orders are used to plan the gross requirements of the supply source.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10394" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Plan Distribution"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10395> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10441> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Cash Flow process consists of monitoring, analyzing, and optimizing the inflows and outflows of cash in the organization. It involves understanding the organization's financial situation to more accurately budget and forecast its cash flow needs. Essentially, it's about having the right amount of money in the right places at the right times. Effective cash flow management empowers organizations to anticipate challenges, seize opportunities, and lay the groundwork for sustainable growth and profitability.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10395" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Cash Flow"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10396> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10441> ;
    skos:definition "Forecasting Financing Requirements process involves estimating the financial needs of the organization. It helps determine sales, costs of customer acquisition, capital for specific projects, and other expenses necessary for effective business management. This pre-emptive forecast enables sound decision-making and ensures that the organization is well-prepared for its financial obligations.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10396" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Forecast Financing Requirements"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10397> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10441> ;
    skos:definition "#lt;div#gt;The Arranging Finance process refers to securing funds or capital for a specific purpose. It involves organizing and structuring financial resources to meet specific requirements.#lt;/div#gt;<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10397" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Arrange Finance"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10398> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10441> ;
    skos:definition "Managing Short-Term Investments process involves handling financial assets that can be easily converted to cash within a relatively short period, typically within five years. Managing Short-term Investments involves the following key decisions:<br/><br/>1. Types of Short-Term Investments <br/>2. Company Perspective <br/>3. Benefits (liquidity, flexibility, etc)<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10398" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Short Term Investment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10399> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10441> ;
    skos:definition "Making and receiving foreign exchange payments involves handling cross-border transactions that require currency exchange. Various payment methods can be used, including wire transfers, global ACH, PayPal, prepaid debit cards, credit cards, and checks.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10399" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Make/Receive Foreign Exchange Payments"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10400> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10441> ;
    skos:definition "Reconciling bank statements involves comparing the organization's financial records with its monthly bank statements. By checking all deposits and withdrawals helps ensure accuracy and gain a clearer picture of the organization's finances. This process is essential for budgeting and identifying any discrepancies between the organization's records and the bank's statement.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10400" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Reconcile Bank & Financial Institution Statements"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10401> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10565> ;
    skos:definition "Formulate Enterprise Privacy Policy process provides the organization the ability to formulate Privacy Policies in a way that assures it business interests with the understanding and consideration of all statutory and regulatory mandates.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10401" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Formulate Enterprise Privacy Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10402> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10565> ;
    skos:definition "Implement Enterprise Privacy Policy process provides the organization the ability to put into effect Privacy Policies in a way that assures it business interests with the understanding and consideration of all statutory and regulatory mandates.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10402" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Implement Enterprise Privacy Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10403> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10565> ;
    skos:definition "Evaluate Enterprise Privacy Policy process provides the organization the ability to collect and analyze information needed to make judgements about contexts, activities, characteristics, or outcomes of privacy policies by virtue of ongoing business needs, and / or impact of external regulations in markets it operates or intends to operate in.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10403" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Evaluate Enterprise Privacy Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10404> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10565> ;
    skos:definition "Change Enterprise Privacy Policy process provides the organization the ability to make changes to its privacy policies on an ongoing basis in order to effectively address its business concerns<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10404" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Change Enterprise Privacy Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10405> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10499> ;
    skos:definition "Administer Asset business activity handles the day-to-day administrative support services for assets.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10405" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Administer Assets"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10406> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10499> ;
    skos:definition "Maintain Asset business activity handles routine and periodic activities that preserve the value of assets. <br/><br/>This business activity will also record and maintain up-to-date information on maintenance and service of assets.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10406" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Maintain Assets"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10407> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10499> ;
    skos:definition "Operate Asset business activity handles the day-to-day running of assets used to conduct ongoing operations of the enterprise.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10407" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Operate Assets"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10408> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10514> ;
    skos:definition "Support Fulfillment business activity guides all order entries, decomposition, workflow tracking and fallout resolution.<br/>Support Fulfillment ensure cross domain and inter vertical orchestration of fulfillment activities, such as between products and services and resources in the enterprise and for reach of its operating markets. It defines how fulfillment is established and completed for requesting customers and entities. This indicates the channels (mutlichannel focused) the organization utilizes, and the levels of support it offers to any engaged party (customers and entities).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10408" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Support Fulfillment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10409> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10424> ;
    skos:definition "Define Employee Personal Identifiable Information Privacy Standards processes ensure that privacy standards are applied to Personal Identifiable Information of employees and/or stakeholders during retention, storage and processing.<br/><br/>This includes all employee roles, stakeholder roles, 3rd party roles and responsibilities, obligations and privileges associated.<br/><br/>This process ensures definition of Personal Identifiable Information Privacy Standards of:<br/>Employees and their responsibilities<br/>Obligations of all employees<br/>Privileges of all employees<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10409" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Employee Personal Identifiable Information Privacy Standards"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10410> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10424> ;
    skos:definition "Define Stakeholder Personal Identifiable Information Privacy Standards processes ensure that privacy standards are applied to Personal Identifiable Information of employees and/or stakeholders during retention, storage and processing.<br/>This includes all stakeholder roles and responsibilities, obligations and privileges associated. This process ensures definition of Personal Identifiable Information Privacy Standards of:<br/>Stakeholders and their responsibilities<br/>Obligations of all stakeholders<br/>Privileges of all stakeholders<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10410" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Stakeholder Personal Identifiable Information Privacy Standards"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10411> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10459> ;
    skos:definition "Monitor Training business activity observes and tracks the enterprises training plans and programs. <br/> Monitor Training business activity allows the enterprise to maintain control of the training processes, while ensuring proactive adaptive response to the business.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10411" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Monitor Training"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10412> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10459> ;
    skos:definition "Evaluate Training Program business activity assess the enterprises training program support its business goals. Evaluate Training Program is the systematic process of collecting information and using that information to improve the enterprises training. Evaluate Training provides feedback to help identify if training programs achieve desired outcomes, and help make decisions about future training programs.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10412" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Evaluate Training Program"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10413> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10575> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10413" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Ensure Legal Compliance"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10414> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10575> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10414" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Carry out Legal requests"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10415> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10575> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10415" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Provide Legal Advice"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10416> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10575> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10416" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Notify Legal Environment Changes"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10417> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10575> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10417" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Legal Actions"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10418> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10172> ;
    skos:definition "Assess Knowledge Management needs business activity analyzes to understand the knowledge needs of enterprise functions, translated the business needs into knowledge management targets and identify knowledge management activities to address the needs. Assess Knowledge Management Needs ensures that assessment of the process and capabilities for knowledge management capture current state of knowledge management activities across enterprise functions. The assessment process solicits input from enterprise functions and 'Evaluate Knowledge Management Performance' to identify improvements for knowledge management.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10418" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Assess Knowledge Management Needs"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10420> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10172> ;
    skos:definition "Evaluate Knowledge Management Performance business activity assesses performance of knowledge management outcomes based on how knowledge management lifecycle and knowledge management operations support the achievement of business goals. Evaluate Knowledge Management Performance supports 'assess knowledge management needs', 'establish knowledge management', and 'knowledge management operations' by preventing repeated missteps, guiding development, and sharing of knowledge to give the enterprise and its business functions a competitive edge.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10420" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Evaluate Knowledge Management Performance"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10422> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10561> ;
    skos:definition "Define Enterprise Privacy Location and Regulation process establish how the relevant privacy regulations must be followed with regards to employees and/or stakeholders. This will include the geographical regions where employees/stakeholders operate from/to; and the location of the Data processing entities.<br/>Define Enterprise Privacy Location and Regulation process is used to:<br/>Identify locations (regulatory jurisdiction) impacted by employee and/or stakeholder privacy concerns.<br/>Define the locations where entities processing information related to employees and/or stakeholders will be located<br/>Define the employee and/or stakeholder privacy regulations that apply to locations<br/>Define the dominant regulation<br/>Define the highest standards that apply for multiple legislative locations<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10422" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Enterprise Privacy Jurisdiction"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10423> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10561> ;
    skos:definition "Define Enterprise Privacy Regulation process is used to establish strategic and operating rules that will typically accompany authoritative mechanism for monitoring and enforcing compliance. This will cover the need to:<br/>Identify legislative boundaries and their impact on business/operations.<br/>Define locations for processing of information<br/>Define privacy regulations that apply to locations<br/>Define the dominant regulation<br/>Define the highest standards that apply for multiple legislative locations.<br/>etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10423" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Enterprise Privacy Regulation"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10425> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10183> ;
    skos:definition "Defines the audit policies and procedures. It will depend on the type of audit like but not limited to Risk audit, Data Management, Data Governance Audit etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10425" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Audit Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10426> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10183> ;
    skos:definition "Define the audit approach to be used depending on the circumstances, as well as the assessment methodology and scoring approach to be used. identify, prioritize and manage audit program .<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10426" ;
