<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10486> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10227> ;
    skos:definition "The objective of this process is to Define Revenue and Cost Assurance Policies and Controls process and to establish and manage a framework of policies and measurable controls that are used to manage the risk associated with revenue and cost assurance, and to optimize the enterprise’s appetite for revenue and cost assurance risk. <br/>These processes are responsible for, but not limited to: <br/>•Establishing and managing a revenue and cost assurance policy framework which is aligned with the overall enterprise goals and objectives<br/>•Developing a framework of controls and KPIs which achieves the defined revenue and cost assurance goals and objectives <br/>•Gaining enterprise-wide commitment to and knowledge of the framework <br/>•Regularly reviewing the revenue and cost assurance framework to ensure that its outcomes remain aligned with the enterprise’s objectives<br/><br/>The Define Revenue and Cost Assurance Policies and Controls has a specific responsibility in developing and defining controls and Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) used for RA, <br/>in conjunction with operational and other processes elsewhere in the enterprise. <br/>Where processes elsewhere in the enterprise have an intrinsic capability to instrument their own performance and behavior (as an aspect of operating effectively within the business), <br/>the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Framework process makes use of this capability, but can also provide guidance to these processes in the form of modified, or additional, KPIs, <br/>required to support the overall role of Revenue and Cost Assurance . This can involve individual process elements throughout the enterprise (as appropriate for the various aspects of Revenue and Cost Assurance that apply), or may involve co-ordination across a number of process elements where Revenue and Cost Assurance acts to provide an integrated or coordinated view of the overall situation. <br/>With regard to KPI definition, the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Framework process establishes the objectives used to identify the minimum level of satisfactory performance required for a given control point or a process from an RA perspective, and works with other process element in the enterprise to effect this. <br/>With regard to development of Revenue and Cost Assurance controls, the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Framework process applies policy-based rules that represent the logical definition of comparisons performed on entities, such as bills and call detail records. <br/>These are used together with Revenue and Cost Assurance KPIs, to identify discrepancies from an RA perspective.<br/><br/><br/>This process was renamed in 24.0 old process name was Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Policy Framework<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10486" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Revenue and Cost Assurance Policies and Controls"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10487> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10227> ;
    skos:definition "While the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Policy Frameworks Process ensures what activities and measures shall be applied and how and the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations Process tracks their outcome, the objective of the Implement Revenue Policies Processes are the detailed implementation steps of the defined KPIs, according to their respective and before-hand evaluated priority, in the manner stated by the RA policy framework, within the technical RA solution tool, considering the evolution of the environment which's probable leak shall sought to be covered. <br/><br/>The process objective is to perform a conception of how to implement a control to meet the requested objectives used to identify the minimum level of satisfactory performance required for a given control point or a process from an RA perspective.<br/>It's aim is to analyze the business process of a given control point, set up and perform an ETL process and develop a Revenue and Cost Assurance Artifact and configure its alarming, most preferably by delivering automated results. <br/><br/>The responsibilities of the processes include, but are not limited to:<br/>•Conception of Business Assurance artifacts like KPIs, controls and metrics<br/>•Ad hoc analysis and results of low level investigations driven by request of stakeholders, triggered alarms or expert judgement<br/>•End-to-end implementation of artifacts, starting with ETL procedure of source data and configuration in mid-layer systems to enable monitoring <br/>•Testing and fine-tuning of the artifacts<br/>•Implemented artifacts (control, metric)<br/>•Documentation (control / metric attributes, dataflow)<br/>•Updated repositories<br/><br/>This process was renamed in 24.0 Old process name was Implement Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10487" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Implement Revenue and Cost Assurance Policies and Controls"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10488> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10227> ;
    skos:definition "This process measures the actual revenue and cost assurance performance at defined control points against the expected performance, report anomalies and manage resolution. <br/>Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes encompass managing, tracking, monitoring, analyzing, controlling and reporting on revenue and cost assurance performance as determined by assessing defined KPIs measured against revenue and cost assurance control points. <br/>If the analysis identifies that a revenue and cost assurance KPI violation has occurred, this causes a Revenue and Cost Assurance violation to be raised, that may in turn raise a Revenue and Cost Assurance Trouble Report. Following on from this, processes are put in place to manage the resolution of the performance violation The Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes will continue to track the revenue and cost assurance trouble report, ensuring that performance is restored to a level required as defined by the acceptable range for the KPIs.<br/>This process was renamed in 24.0 Old process name was Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations and then back to Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations in 25.0<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10488" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10489> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10227> ;
    skos:definition "The objectives of the Support Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes are twofold: <br/>•support the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes by managing requirements for infrastructure to support the operational processes, and<br/>•monitoring, managing and reporting on the capability of the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes <br/><br/>The responsibilities of the processes include, but are not limited to: <br/>•Developing and maintaining a repository of revenue and cost assurance KPIs to support the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes<br/>•Monitoring and analyzing the report produced by Operations processes to identify potential revenue and cost assurance problems that may be arising across operational processes as a whole<br/>•Establishing and managing revenue and cost assurance data collection schedules, including managing the collection of the necessary information from the Resource Data Collection & Distribution processes, to support proactive monitoring and analysis activity, and requests from <br/>Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes Implement Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes for additional data to support revenue and cost assurance performance analysis<br/>•Monitoring of the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes and associated costs (including to where the processes extend to infrastructure, deployed and managed by third parties), and reporting on the capability of the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes<br/>•Establishing and managing resource performance notification facilities and lists to support the Manage Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations notification and reporting processes and the Implement Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations processes <br/>•Creating, deploying, modifying and/or upgrading of revenue and cost assurance infrastructure deployment support tools and processes for new and/or modified revenue and cost assurance infrastructure <br/>•Authoring, reviewing and approving operational procedures developed by Resource Development & processes prior to resource infrastructure deployment<br/>•Testing and acceptance of new and/or modified revenue and cost assurance infrastructure support tools as part of the handover procedure from the Resource Development & processes <br/>•Detecting revenue and cost assurance infrastructure operational limitations and/or deployment incompatibilities and providing requirements to address these aspects to Resource Development & processes<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10489" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Support Revenue and Cost Assurance Operations"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10495> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10581> ;
    skos:definition "Enterprise Capacity Planning business process activity handle the tasks of balancing available \"resources\" against value streams need in order to meet the enterprises' demand management program.<br/>Enterprise Capacity Planning maintains a holistic view across the enterprise to ensure a match of supply with demand given all the resources available to the enterprise. It receives reports from all value streams (product/service and resource), and supports the overarching capacity management policies.<br/>Enterprise Capacity Planning impacts on all the enterprise, it's projects, and measures and tracks the allocation and use of capacity based on well defined capacity management strategy.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10495" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Enterprise Capacity Planning"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10496> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10581> ;
    skos:definition "Enterprise Capacity Management Requirement business activity help to identify and deal with the Enterprises demand program to support any and all of the value streams, including products, service and resources altogether.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10496" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Enterprise Capacity Management Requirement"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10503> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10185> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Capital Investment business activity directs and controls corporate expenditure of money to fund the enterprises long-term growth. <br/><br/>Manage Capital Investment can facilitate enterprises acquisition of permanent fixed assets such as real estate and equipment, or provide diversification leveraging Manage Capital Investment business activity. This includes diversification strategies like replacements and modernization.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10503" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Capital Investment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10505> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10185> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Liquidity business activity directs and controls corporate visibility into the enterprise cash position. <br/><br/>Manage Liquidity can be long-term, but for short-term it enables the enterprise to improve decision-making. Visibility into a firm's cash and liquidity position allows corporate treasurers to analyze surplus funds to make better investment and borrowing decisions.<br/><br/>This business activity handles tasks make decisions around working capital and operating cashflows (current assets and current liabilities) in order to avoid disrupting the enterprises business operations. These activities can extend to getting additional credit lines or activating liquidity backups.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10505" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Liquidity"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10506> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10185> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Managerial Accounting business activity directs, analyzes and communicates financial data to corporate managers who use the information to make business decisions.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10506" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Managerial Accounting"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10507> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10338> ;
    skos:definition "Metric Dimension Specification defines and maintains for each Metric: categories (organizational or technical classifications), dimensions (time, space, user groups, priority levels, …), cross-references, dependencies, and tree hierarchies which characterize the Metric with respect to other Metrics.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10507" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define & Maintain Metric Dimension Specifications"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10508> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10338> ;
    skos:definition "Metric Definition Specification defines and maintains the following for each Metric: one or multiple IDs (for different repositories or identification schemes), one or multiple names (for different naming schemes), high-level description, business value, comments, and status data (entry date, last-used date, active/inactive, maturity level, validity period, etc.).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10508" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Specify Metric Definition"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10516> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10443> ;
    skos:definition "Analyze Change business activity examine changes planned based on enterprise needs, risks and benefits.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10516" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Analyze Change"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10517> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10443> ;
    skos:definition "Authorize Change business activity endorse and permit a planned change for implementation based on enterprise needs in line with risk plans.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10517" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Authorize Change"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10530> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10173> ;
    skos:definition "Develop the Workforce processes support the definition of the organization of the enterprise and coordinate its reorganizations. These processes can apply for the overall organization, can define the organization of single business units, or at least can ensure coherency and/or guarantee support to specific processes defining<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10530" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Develop the Workforce"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10534> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10173> ;
    skos:definition "Report Workforce process is responsible for preparing the statistical data on quality, productivity, and efficiency for the services performed by the involved employees and/or third parties. These processes record, analyze, and assess the workforce in order to provide specialized summaries of the efficiency and effectiveness of the overall Workforce processes. These specialized summaries can be specific reports required by specific audiences, as well as reporting on associated costs of the Manage Workforce processes.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10534" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Report Workforce"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10535> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10497> ;
    skos:definition "Establish Asset Catalog business activity defines and organizes different assets into classes and their properties for effective control, operations and valuation.<br/><br/>Establish Asset Catalog will identify types of assets, asset properties, asset access need etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10535" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Establish Asset Catalog"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10536> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10497> ;
    skos:definition "Establish Asset Lifecycle Management business activity support optimizing the value derived from assets through their lifetime. <br/><br/>Establish Asset Lifecycle Management business activity ensures that each asset, based on the catalog type, has a lifecycle that covers planning, acquisition, operation & maintenance, and disposal/decommissioning.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10536" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Establish Asset Management LCM"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10537> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10497> ;
    skos:definition "Establish Asset Management Policy defines the key principles, responsibilities and approach to all asset catalog management types and categories.<br/><br/>Effectively executing Establish Asset Management Policy address: scope and purpose, definitions of policies, capitalization thresholds, additions, transfers, disposals and losses, inventory and periodic audits/assessment of conditions and maintenance and repair.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10537" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Establish Asset Management Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10538> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10497> ;
    skos:definition "Budget Asset business activity enables the organization to capture new assets into the organizations budget. <br/><br/>Budget Asset business activity establish dimensions to use in asset budgeting and the relationship to business line activities; support Cataloging Assets and Capital acquisition planning.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10538" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Budget Assets"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10539> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10245> ;
    skos:definition "Define Research Topic business activity describes the subject or issue that a researcher must focus on when conducting research. Define Research Topic provides a well-defined research topic as starting point of every successful research project. The choice of a topic is an ongoing process by which researchers explore, define, and refine ideas.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10539" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Research Topic"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10540> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10245> ;
    skos:definition "Identify Research Objectives business activity pinpoint and research goals and targets and discern the focus of research. This business activity includes breaking down the research focus into research targets and defining criteria to evaluate research objectives.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10540" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Identify Research objectives"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10541> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10245> ;
    skos:definition "Select Research Method business activity match the best research method to research objectives. Select Research Method activity may take input from 'Identify Research Topic' and 'Identify Research Objectives' to understand the best research analysis option (qualitative research, quantitative research a mix of both) to support the research methodology.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10541" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Select Research Method"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10542> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10245> ;
    skos:definition "Build Research Capacity business activity develops the abilities and skills enabling the enterprise to perform research. Build Research Capacity addresses individual and enterprise-wide research capacity development which leads to higher levels of skills and greater ability to perform research.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10542" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Build Research Capacity"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10543> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10245> ;
    skos:definition "Develop Research Brief business activity builds out the research briefings to provide a concise summary of research knowledge on a particular topic. Develop Research Brief business activity will summarize research evidence in an accessible form to the research audience.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10543" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Develop Research Brief"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10544> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10245> ;
    skos:definition "Establish Research timeline business activity define clear schedules, start and end dates/times for a research plan.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10544" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Establish Research timeline"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10545> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10245> ;
    skos:definition "Define Research Report Requirement business activity describe the written or formal outcome of findings and observation of the research.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10545" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Define Research Report Requirement"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10546> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10520> ;
    skos:definition "Establish Compliance Policy business activity develops and oversees implementation of compliance policy that apply to all activities of the enterprise to prevent, detect, monitor and report any compliance program in terms of the organization and its management. <br/><br/>Establish Compliance Policy activity interact with Managing Legal and Regulatory Requirements, Managing Risks and Managing Internal Controls. This business activity uses knowledge of legal regulations and obligations under which an enterprise is established, and operates.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10546" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Establish Compliance Policy"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10547> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10520> ;
    skos:definition "Monitor Compliance business activity is in charge of identifying, observing and keeping tracking of quality assurance tests that check how well the enterprises' business operations meet regulatory and internal process and procedural obligations.<br/><br/>Monitor Compliance business activity include tasks that develop compliance testing, also known as conformance testing for periodic, independent, and objective assessment of compliance-related processes and/or controls. Monitor Compliance plays a major role in helping to detect vulnerabilities in existing compliance risk management controls.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10547" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Monitor Compliance"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10548> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10520> ;
    skos:definition "Detect Compliance Changes business activity is in charge of discovering differences between Established Compliance Policies and ongoing enterprise operations.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10548" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Detect Compliance Changes"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10549> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10520> ;
    skos:definition "Report Compliance State business activity is in charge of providing documented evidence to show the enterprise and its business is compliant with established compliance policy requirements put in place.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10549" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Report Compliance State"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10550> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10579> ;
    skos:definition "Define/select, develop and deploy the enterprise architecture methodology, which is a framework that identifies the reference models, their relationships to each other, and the architecture management processes used to establish and maintain the enterprise architecture. The framework contains the policies, guidelines, documentation templates and approaches to be used throughout the enterprise. Enterprise Architecture Management processes define, develop, manage and maintain the enterprise architecture, which is the model describing the enterprise in all its facets.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10550" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Enterprise Architecture Methodology"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10551> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10579> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10551" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Co-ordinate Enterprise Architecture"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10552> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10579> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10552" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Enterprise Architecture Toolsets and Associated Standards"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10553> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10579> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10553" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage & Administer Architecture Repositories"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10554> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10579> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10554" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Architecture Skillsets"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10555> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10579> ;
    skos:definition "Provides the reference source for the enterprise Standard Operating Environment that is the collection of applications, hardware, software and network components that have been standardized for use across the enterprise. The business strategies and plans provide a key starting point for the development and direction provided. Note that enterprise architecture management covers both IT and network technologies, and the processes impact other areas within the eTOM model, such as Knowledge Management and Process Architecture Management.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10555" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Provide Reference Source for Standard Operating Environment"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10556> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10579> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10556" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Co-ordinate Architecture Review"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10557> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10339> ;
    skos:definition "Metric Definition Measure Specification specifies details for measuring a Metric: prose-style and spreadsheet-style calculation formulas and equations (possibly including other Metrics), raw data sources, raw data capture methods (including APIs), measurement units.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10557" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Specify Metric Definition Measure"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10558> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10339> ;
    skos:definition "Metric Definition Measure Threshold Specification defines threshold values and intervals, with comparators for direction of threshold-crossing, applicable to a given Metric. Metric Definition Measure Threshold Specification also specifies threshold-crossing rules and consequences (actions to be performed, notifications to be sent).<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10558" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Specify Metric Definition Measure Threshold"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10559> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10604> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Enterprise Activity Results business activity is in charge of directing and controlling expected outcome of implementation of enterprise assets or resources.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10559" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Enterprise Activity Results"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10560> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10604> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Enterprise Resource Allocation business activity is in charge of directing and controlling the distribution of resources aimed at delivering planned results.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10560" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Enterprise Resource Allocation"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10566> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10458> ;
    skos:definition "Administer Training Program business activity manages the responsibility for the implementation of the training program. Administer Training Program is responsible for the coordination of trainers with training capability and facility. It administers the recordkeeping that tracks training capability, training facility, training participation progress, as well as administrating and budgeting tasks associated with training programs.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10566" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Administer Training Program"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10567> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10458> ;
    skos:definition "Select Training Method business activity makes a choice of the method of training to be used in a training program. Select Training Method is responsible for guiding selection of the most appropriate training method(s). It takes input from the training assessment activity based on requirements identified between needs and gaps, and recommendations made during the Needs Analysis or training design activities.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10567" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Select Training Method"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10569> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10522> ;
    skos:definition "Execute Contract business activity is in charge of ensuring an enterprise business contract is fully signed by the contracting parties in order to formalize the contractual relationship.<br/>To “execute a contract” means to perform the actions necessary to complete the contract’s terms or to sign a contract, making it legally binding. In legal terms.<br/> An executed contract refers to:<br/>• Signing: When all parties involved in the contract have agreed upon the terms and have signed the document, it is considered executed. <br/>• Fulfillment: An executed contract can also mean that all obligations outlined in the contract have been met by the parties involved.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10569" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Execute Contract"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10570> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10522> ;
    skos:definition "Analyze Contract business activity is in charge of examining and tracking all information within a contract over its lifecycle and the impact or implications on the enterprises ongoing concerns. <br/>Analyze Contract business activity is effectively used throughout the contract lifecycle to address the enterprises’ need to track implications at any point in time (financial or related to the status of the contract) to ensure that the clauses remain consistent and in line with any changes in the enterprises’ operating policy.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10570" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Analyze Contract"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10583> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10438> ;
    skos:definition "The Develop Budgets activity involves creating financial plans for a specific period to ensure the enterprise’s financial resources are used effectively and efficiently. This includes setting financial goals, estimating revenues and expenses, and allocating financial resources to various departments and projects. The main objectives are to align the budget with the enterprise’s strategic goals, control expenditures, and measure financial performance to achieve business objectives.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10583" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Develop Budgets"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10584> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10438> ;
    skos:definition "Allocate Financial Resources process involves distributing the enterprise’s financial resources to various departments, projects, or activities. The key steps include identifying financial needs, allocating the budget based on priorities, and continuously monitoring and adjusting the allocations. The main goals are to ensure optimal financial resource utilization, align financial allocations with strategic goals, and maintain financial control.<br/><br/>This process was renamed in 24.5 old name was Manage Resource Allocation<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10584" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Allocate Financial Resources"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10585> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10438> ;
    skos:definition "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:Lato, \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:15px;\"><span style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px;display:inline !important;float:none;font-style:normal;font-variant-caps:normal;font-variant-ligatures:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;orphans:2;text-align:start;text-decoration-color:initial;text-decoration-style:initial;text-decoration-thickness:initial;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;widows:2;word-spacing:0px;\">The Design Capital Structure process involves determining the best mix of debt, equity, and other financial instruments to fund an enterprise’s operations and growth. The key steps include assessing financial needs, identifying funding sources, analyzing costs and risks, and optimizing the capital mix. The main goals are to minimize the cost of capital, manage risks, and align the capital structure with the enterprise’s long-term financial goals.</span></span><br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10585" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Design Capital Structure"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10586> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10438> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Financial Risk includes tasks to identify existing and potential financial risks that could negatively impact the organization’s financial profile, assess and quantify financial risks to prioritize them based on their impact, define and implement strategies to control financial threats, and continuously monitor the effectiveness of strategies that reduce financial risk. This enables the enterprise to clearly understand its financial risk profile, and develop approach to de-risk financial risks.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10586" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Financial Risk"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10597> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10515> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Supply Chain Storage business activity handles the allocation and safe keeping of supplies.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10597" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Supply Chain Storage"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10598> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10515> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Supply Chain Transport business activity handles the allocation and safe transport of supplies.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10598" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Supply Chain Transport"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10599> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10513> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Inbound Supplies activity support receiving inbound supplies.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10599" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Inbound Supplies"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10600> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10513> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Inventory supports activities for planning and executing inventory to support core business process inventory management activities.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10600" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Inventory"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10601> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10513> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Outbound Suppliers'' activity support preparing and shipping supplies to their intended destinations.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10601" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Outbound Supplies"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10602> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10513> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Supply Routing or (Cross Docking) handle the direct crossing of supplies received with supplies issuing.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10602" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Supply Routing"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10612> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10568> ;
    skos:definition "Consolidate Contract business activity is in charge of combining contracts for similar products and/or services to form one single, all encompassing contract. <br/><br/>Consolidate Contract business activity supports Prepare Contract business activity by helping to reduce contract administration (executing, analyzing) and associated enterprise costs.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10612" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Consolidate Contracts"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10613> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10568> ;
    skos:definition "Negotiate Contract business activity is in charge of arranging for or bring about by discussion and settlement of contract terms.<br/>Negotiate Contract involves several key steps to ensure the involved parties reach a mutually beneficial agreement. <br/>It involves the following tasks: <br/>• Setting the right tone from the beginning with a positive and professional attitude. <br/>• Discussion and bargaining by exchange of offers and counteroffers. <br/>• Problem solving addressing any disagreements or obstacles.<br/>• Finalizing the contract ensuring that all negotiated points are clearly stated.<br/>After the contract is signed, following up on the implementation of the contract terms to ensure compliance and address any issues promptly is important.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10613" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Negotiate Contract"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10614> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10572> ;
    skos:definition "Responsible for ensuring the enterprise's position within the community, or communities, within which it operates. This includes local activities with, and financial and other support for, schools, libraries, hospitals, emergency services, etc.; concern for the immediate environment; visibility at local events; etc.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10614" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Ensure Community Visibility"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10615> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10572> ;
    skos:definition "Not used for this process element.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10615" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Communicate Community Messaging"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10616> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10572> ;
    skos:definition "Handle contact with customer interest groups and customer representatives, as well as dealing with public relations and community relations contacts made to the enterprise. These processes also influence the privacy policy for the enterprise.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10616" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Handle Community Contacts"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10617> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10475> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Master Data Integration business activity direct and control tasks to syndicate master data for a harmonized view across all business applications. Manage Master Data Integration ensure that master data is consistently integrated across various systems in an organization with the aim of achieving a coherent enterprise data model with common semantics that can be used to exchange data between business applications. This business activity involves data mapping, transformation, and loading (ETL), data synchronization, conflict resolution, and distributing master data based on a common model for end-to-end process integration.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10617" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Master Data Integration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10618> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10475> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Master Data Quality business activity direct and control tasks to ensure and improve the accuracy, completeness, and consistency of master data.<br/><br/>Manage Master Data Quality ensure the reliability of business decisions made based on the information/data, comply with regulations, and increase operational efficiency. It involves activities such as data profiling, data cleansing, data enrichment, and ongoing data quality monitoring.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10618" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Master Data Quality"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10620> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10619> ;
    skos:definition "Create Master Data business activity is responsible for initiating a new set of master data, and ensuring that new master data is accurate, consistent, and relevant to the business.<br/> <br/>Create Master Data involves identifying master data, evaluating data sources, analyzing metadata, and analyzing underlying master data lifecycle(s) according to business goals.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10620" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Create Master Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10621> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10619> ;
    skos:definition "Update Master Data business activity is responsible for making changes to existing master data to ensure it remains accurate and up-to-date.<br/> <br/>Update Master Data maintains the integrity of the master data, ensuring it reflects current business realities, and improves business activities and events.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10621" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Update Master Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10622> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10619> ;
    skos:definition "Collect Master Data business activity is responsible for gathering master data from various sources.<br/><br/>Collect Master Data ensures data's accuracy, completeness, and relevance to the organization based on a well-defined scope. It involves defining the role of the master data, choosing the data collection method, planning data collection procedures, and collecting the data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10622" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Collect Master Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10623> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10619> ;
    skos:definition "Remove Master Data business activity is responsible for deleting or deactivating master data that is no longer needed in order to maintain the relevancy of master data, comply with data retention policies, and optimize storage resources.<br/> <br/>Remove Master Data business activity involves cleaning up to remove or deactivate master data records and disassociating mastership of such data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10623" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Remove Master Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10624> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10476> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Transactional Data Integration business activity directs and controls tasks to ensure transactional data is consistently integrated across various systems in an organization.<br/> <br/>Manage Transactional Data Integration improves data consistency, reduce redundancy, and ensure that all systems are using the same, most up-to-date version of data.<br/>It includes activities that do data mapping, data transformation, data loading (ETL), data synchronization, and data conflict resolution.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10624" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Transactional Data Integration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10625> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10476> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Transactional Data Quality business activity direct and control tasks to ensure the accuracy, completeness, and consistency of transactional data.<br/><br/>Manage Transactional Data Quality improve the reliability of business decisions made based on the data, comply with regulations, and increase operational efficiency. It includes activities that perform transactional data profiling, transactional data cleansing, transactional data enrichment, and ongoing transactional data quality monitoring.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10625" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Transactional Data Quality"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10627> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10626> ;
    skos:definition "Create Transactional Data business activity is responsible for generating and data entry of new transactional data for storage accurately and in a timely fashion.<br/><br/>Create Transactional Data includes creating new business records, create data for a sales transaction, or any event that needs to be recorded.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10627" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Create Transactional Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10628> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10626> ;
    skos:definition "Update Transactional Data ensure changes or corrections in the transaction data.<br/><br/>Update Transactional Data ensure that changes to transaction data can maintain accuracy and relevance of the underlying transaction.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10628" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Update Transactional Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10629> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10626> ;
    skos:definition "Collect Transactional Data business activity is responsible for gathering transactional data for onward processing (analysis and reporting).<br/><br/>Collect Transactional Data involves extracting transactional data from various sources, transforming it into a suitable format, and loading it into appropriate storage to support decision-making with timely and reliable information.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10629" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Collect Transactional Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10630> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10626> ;
    skos:definition "Remove Transactional Data business activity is responsible for deleting transactional data that is no longer needed, in compliance with data retention policies and regulations.<br/><br/>Remove Transactional Data includes optimization of transactional data management performance, and ensuring compliance with data security, retention, and privacy regulations and laws.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10630" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Remove Transactional Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10631> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10477> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Reference Data Integration business activity directs and controls the seamless integration of reference data (such as location, currency, transaction codes, units, etc) across various systems and platforms within an organization.<br/><br/>Manage Reference Data Integration ensures that reference data is consistently and accurately represented across all systems, thereby reducing discrepancies and improving data integrity. Manage Reference Data Integration facilitates efficient data sharing and synchronization across different business units and includes activities that map reference data, consolidate reference data, and establish reference data integration protocols.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10631" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Reference Data Integration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10632> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10477> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Reference Data Quality business activity directs and controls tasks to maintain and enhance the quality of reference data and information.<br/><br/>Manage Reference Data Quality ensures reference data is accurate, complete, timely, and relevant for the business operations. It improves reference data usage, reduces reference data errors, and enhances operational efficiency through tasks such as reference data validation, reference data cleansing, reference data enrichment, and the implementation of reference data quality metrics and controls.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10632" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Reference Data Quality"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10634> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10633> ;
    skos:definition "Create Reference Data business task is responsible for generating new reference data that can be used across various systems and applications within an organization.<br/> <br/>Create Reference Data ensures that the new reference data is accurate, consistent, and relevant to the business. This involves defining the reference data elements, setting up the reference data structure, and populating reference data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10634" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Create Reference Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10635> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10633> ;
    skos:definition "Update Reference Data business task is responsible for making changes to existing reference data to ensure it remains accurate and up-to-date.<br/><br/>Update Reference Data ensures that reference data maintains the integrity of the data, ensure reference data reflects current business realities, and improves the business operations. This includes transactions or developing actions to update reference data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10635" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Update Reference Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10636> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10633> ;
    skos:definition "Collect Reference Data business task is responsible for gathering reference data from various sources to be used in the organization.<br/> <br/>Collect Reference Data ensures that reference data is accurate, complete, and relevant to the organization and its operations. This involves defining the aim of collecting reference data, choosing the reference data collection method, planning reference data collection procedures, and collecting the reference data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10636" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Collect Reference Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10637> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10633> ;
    skos:definition "Remove Reference Data business task is responsible for deleting or remove reference data that is no longer needed.<br/><br/>Remove Reference Data supports the need to maintain the relevancy of the reference data, comply with data retention policies, and optimize data storage resources. This includes reference data cleanup to remove or unlink reference data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10637" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Remove Reference Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10638> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10478> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Unstructured Data Integration business activity directs and control tasks to connect to many different sources of unstructured business/operational data, extract that data, and store it in a suitable destination, such as a data lake or data warehouse.<br/><br/>Manage Unstructured Data Integration improve the consistency of unstructured data, provide comprehensive unstructured data access, and deliver timely, accurate unstructured data for decision support. This includes extracting reference data from sources, transforming unstructured data to fit operational needs, and loading unstructured data into target (database, data mart, or data warehouse) storage systems.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10638" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Unstructured Data Integration"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10639> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10478> ;
    skos:definition "Manage Unstructured Data Quality is responsible for ensuring high quality and trust of unstructured data across the enterprise.<br/> <br/>Manage Unstructured Data Quality tasks include unstructured data cleansing, unstructured data transformation, and unstructured data integration.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10639" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Manage Unstructured Data Quality"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10641> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10640> ;
    skos:definition "Create Unstructured Data task is responsible for generating new unstructured data, and ensuring that new unstructured data is accurate and consistent.<br/> <br/>Create Unstructured Data involves defining the unstructured data elements, setting up the unstructured data structure, and populating the data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10641" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Create Unstructured Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10642> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10640> ;
    skos:definition "Update Unstructured Data task is responsible for making changes to existing unstructured data to ensure it remains accurate and up-to-date.<br/> <br/>Update Unstructured Data maintains the integrity of unstructured data, ensuring it reflects current realities, and improves the businesses operations. It involves using transactions or developing custom initiatives to update unstructured data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10642" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Update Unstructured Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10643> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10640> ;
    skos:definition "Collect Unstructured Data task is responsible for gathering unstructured data from various sources to be used in the organization.<br/> <br/>Collect Unstructured Data ensures unstructured data is accurate, complete, and relevant to the organization. It includes tasks to define the aim of the collecting unstructured data, choosing the unstructured data collection method, planning unstructured data collection procedures, and collecting the unstructured data.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10643" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Collect Unstructured Data"@en .

<http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10644> a skos:Concept ;
    skos:broader <http://ots.local/thesaurus/etom/etom_EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10640> ;
    skos:definition "Remove Unstructured Data task is responsible for deleting or removing unstructured data that is no longer needed according to the enterprise's data management policies.<br/><br/>Remove Unstructured Data supports activities to maintain the relevancy of data, comply with data retention policies, and optimize storage resources. This includes unstructured data removal.<br/>"@en ;
    skos:inScheme thes:etom ;
    skos:notation "etom:EARoot_EA5_EA1_EA8_EA10644" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Remove Unstructured Data"@en .

